<TEXT>
republican vice presidential candidate dan quayle still the 
center of controversy on the campaign circuit shrugged off his 
latest problem resume inflation as democratic presidential 
nominee michael dukakis planned to address a civil rights rally of 
thousands in the nations capital 
meanwhile vice president george bush on friday lashed back at 
dukakis for his criticism of the reagan administrations handling 
of drug problems and took up the defense of his embattled running 
mate whom he had not mentioned by name in two previous days of 
campaigning 
dukakis pondering todays commemoration of the 25th anniversary 
of the march on washington led by the rev martin luther king jr 
said of the 1963 event 
it was one of the great historic events in the history of this 
country and it came at a time when black people and minority 
citizens were facing terrible discrimination it was an historic 
event which triggered a civil rights revolution in this country 
the massachusetts governor who spent friday attending to state 
business was to march in the procession today and speak at a 
rally afterward among those planning to attend were coretta scott 
king the widow of the slain civil rights leader and jesse 
jackson dukakis onetime rival for the democratic presidential 
nomination 
jackson lauded the democratic ticket of dukakis and sen lloyd 
bentsen of texas saying we do have a choice and chance in 
november dukakis and bentsen represent an alternative a chance to 
change 
neither bush nor quayle had responded to an invitation to join 
the commemoration said ofield dukes a spokesman for march 
organizers 
bushs schedule for today called for him to remain in his 
adopted state of texas while quayle was expected to make several 
stops in california 
quayle buoyed by a warm welcome from the veterans of foreign 
wars earlier this week was ready to focus on issues and move on 
from questions about whether he joined the national guard in 1969 
at the height of the vietnam war to duck combat duty and whether 
he had help from his influential family in getting into the guard 
but another question arose friday this one concerning what he 
was doing the following two years 1970 and 1971 
the indiana senator acknowledged friday that an entry on his 
official biography that portrays him as indianas chief consumer 
investigator for those two years was inaccurate but he said 
his senate staff was responsible for the document and that the 
matter was unimportant 
all of these issues are side events many of them are 
untrue quayle said in billings mont regarding reporters 
questions about his erroneous biography and other issues that have 
dogged his campaign 
the law creating the consumer unit passed april 14 1971 and 
the division did not being operations until july 1 1971 indiana 
officials said quayle served as chief investigator from july until 
midseptember 
quayle also fended off questions about his academic record and 
said he would not authorize their public release 
i dont want you to go through and pore over all those 
mediocre grades i got he said 
the senator got a boost from bush who told a rally in eastern 
texas that quayle would be an outstanding vice president and 
bush later called him to discuss the campaign 
bush also told the rally that it was an insult for dukakis 
to refer to president reagans drug policies as criminal and 
absurd when thousands of federal and local law enforcement 
officials are putting their lives on the line every single day to 
stop the narcotics flow 
dukakis is the governor who vetoed the mandatory sentencing 
for drug dealers bush said he opposes capital punishment for 
drug king pins and he fought tooth and nail to keep that 
outrageous furlough program that lets murderers rapists and drug 
dealers out on appeal 
bentsen meanwhile pressed for southern votes friday by 
stressing the democratic tickets interest in maintaining americas 
military strength 
we want to build up americas military might but once again 
it has to be bipartisan cooperation he told a crowd of 1000 
arkansas democrats adding that he was fed up with republicans 
trying to portray the democrats as weak on defense 
bentsen arrived at the arkansas state democratic convention in a 
small twoengine airplane after his campaign jet was grounded in 
mississippi he was forced to cancel a trip to atlanta because of 
airplane trouble 
aircraft troubles previously created havoc with the media 
representatives attempting to follow bush on the campaign trail 
and prompted the bush campaign to change charter airlines 
