<TEXT>
eastern airlines will learn tuesday whether it 
can inaugurate its september schedule calling for curtailment of 
service to 14 cities at a savings of some 57 million 
us district judge barrington d parker on friday extended his 
order preventing eastern airlines from firing some 4000 workers 
whose unions alleged in a lawsuit that easterns parent company 
texas air corp deliberately dismantled the financially troubled 
passenger carrier to rid it of organized labor 
john gallagher an attorney for eastern attempted repeatedly 
without success to get parker to elaborate on his twopage order in 
which he said the three unions suing eastern were entitled to 
relief 
gallagher complained that the airlines business was hurting due 
to news reports that parkers order had blocked the companys plans 
to end service to 14 cities 
i cant help what the newspapers are reporting parker said 
you should know better than to rely on the newspapers 
if you could tell me at this point what i am going to do on 
tuesday you are a better man than i said parker i dont 
know 
gallagher told the judge later our client is being prejudiced 
in the marketplace our client does not know what it can or cannot 
do 
parker refused to reply in detail saying only i am working 
on the opinion 
in his friday order parker essentially continued the temporary 
restraining order he issued aug 4 prohibiting eastern from firing 
the 4000 workers but not preventing the company from curtailing 
service to 14 cities 
gallagher said the september schedule set to go into effect 
next wednesday would save eastern 50 million in the change of 
schedules and 7 million in salaries 
we will appeal he said of parkers ruling 
capt jack bavis a representative of the air line pilots 
association called the judges decision a victory for 40000 
eastern employees for once justice is working for the little 
people not just the big people 
jonathan cohen an attorney for the association also considered 
parkers decision a victory 
we know now that at least the temporary restraining order will 
be extended that means 4000 jobs he said after the court 
hearing but he parker said he is considering other issues the 
tro temporary restraining order is the minimum we are 
optimistic 
asked whether eastern can close down its service in the 14 
cities cohen said the company has to be cautious they are 
operating at a risk with what they do he said he has everything 
under consideration 
earlier karen ceremsak a spokeswoman for the miamibased 
eastern said in a statement that the company believes the unions 
are not entitled to relief of any sort and we expect we will be 
filing an appeal at the appropriate time 
the statement said the airline would take no action against the 
employees pending clarifications of what our obligation will be 
under terms of the ruling 
the pilots association the international association of 
machinists and the transport workers union of america filed suit 
earlier this month accusing frank lorenzos texas air of 
deliberately taking eastern apart to get rid of organized labor at 
the carrier 
the 81page suit filed in us district court here said texas 
air was trying to undermine the unions legal right to represent 
eastern employees by transferring the airlines assets to other 
subsidiaries of the parent 
eastern which has lost about 1 billion over the past 10 years 
posted a second quarter net loss of 898 million compared with 
net income of 271 million a year earlier easterns revenue in 
the most recent quarter declined to 1 billion from 12 billion 
the eastern plan announced july 22 also calls for elimination 
of 140 of its 1225 daily flights to help cut costs 
the plan would end nearly all operations at kansas city 
easterns principal hub for the western united states and 
dramatically reduce flights at its philadelphia hub flights to 14 
cities also would be dropped under the plan 
the suit said the eastern plan violated the railway labor act 
and federal and state security laws 
the complaint charged that the transfer of some eastern air 
routes planes and airport gate rights to other subsidiaries such 
as continental was part of a scheme to weaken the iams power to 
represent eastern employees 
