two weeks for more talks 
the timetable is the key both to ending fighting between 
cubanbacked angolan forces and south africa and to independence 
for southwest africa angolas southern neighbor that is also 
known as namibia 
sources in the south african delegation said substantial 
progress was made on cuban withdrawal the united states which 
mediated the talks proposed that the cubans pull out within 18 
months a compromise the angolan delegation took home to luanda 
overnight thursday for consideration by its marxist government 
