<TEXT>
damaged orings destined for space shuttle 
rockets were apparently sabotaged but they were caught before they 
could be installed in boosters officials said as nasa and the fbi 
investigated 
however a former morton thiokol employee told a television 
station friday that a deliberately cut oring was put in a rocket 
segment being assembled at the booster makers northern utah plant 
the 1986 challenger disaster was blamed on a faulty oring that 
allowed superhot exhaust gases to escape through a booster joint 
igniting the shuttles external fuel tank and killing the 
sevenmember crew 
a very small number of orings that appeared to have been 
deliberately cut were discovered in june said hydrapak inc vice 
president james dockstader whose company makes the rings under 
contract to morton thiokol 
the discovery was immediately reported to the fbi the national 
aeronautics and space administration and morton thiokol 
dockstader said friday 
the fbi is investigating the possibility of sabotage said agent 
cal clegg who declined to elaborate 
nasa inspector general bill colvin likewise refused to discuss 
his agencys probe but said nasa officials believed none of the 
damaged orings ever reached morton thiokol and that their 
discovery would not affect plans to launch shuttle discovery 
the nations first shuttle mission since the challenger tragedy 
is expected to be scheduled for late next month or early october 
dockstader said a check determined none of the flawed seals was 
shipped from hydrapaks plant in suburban west jordan to morton 
thiokol dockstader said 
the damaged orings were immediately secured dockstader 
said no orings have been shipped from hydrapak with any kind of 
damage 
hydrapak has taken steps to prevent similar incidents in the 
future and is confident the problem is now resolved he added 
nasa spokesman dwayne brown said extensive inspection and 
quality control procedures found the damage before the orings 
left hydrapaks plant 
but a former morton thiokol employee told television station 
ktvx he saw a flawed oring placed in a rocket segment 
i was there when they received the damaged oring and it was 
labeled from hydrapak and it was in a package that had gone 
