at oxford university as a rhodes scholar we exchanged letters 
and he described it there as cold and rainy it was hard duty 
said sieverts 
publicly dukakis is proud of his military record it was 
after the truce had been signed but at a time when korea was very 
much on a wartime footing im very proud of that service he 
said recently 
levine recalled that it was pretty unpleasant for example 
there wasnt much water it was restricted because of the fear of 
infections so that meant you got water in cans and you didnt get 
many showers 
the countryside was desolate both as a consequence of the war 
