examination of the b1 bomber program last year 
the air forces and contractors attention to priority parts 
has resolved some parts problems but a more systematic approach 
would ensure early and appropriate attention to the problem 
parts the report said 
two weeks ago aspin said it might be necessary to halt spending 
on the bomber rather than pay for expensive repairs 
the earlier congressional budget office report on the bomber 
said problems center around electronic countermeasures the 
complex computerdriven system that defends the plane against 
attack as it flies on its mission 
the b1 program was killed by president carter in 1977 but 
resurrected by president reagan four years later because reagan 
said the plane was needed as a successor to the aging b52 
