beneath 40yearold murals depicting the end of 
wars and plagues the envoys of warring iran and iraq entered the 
grand chamber separately and skeptically to sit at opposite tables 
for peace talks 
they faced each other across a gulf of gray carpeting 15 feet 
wide and a another gulf of centuriesold hatred they called each 
other monsieur excellency and colleague but after 
two days of direct and separate talks under un auspices both 
sides remained far apart 
ater eight years of the war and more than a thousand years of 
arabpersian enmity no one expected the long peace process to be 
